<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-435-058  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 435 058.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Federal Computer Week  July 17 1989 v3 n29 p31(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Tobias pushes for better federal staffing policies. (NationalTreasury Employees Union pres Robert Tobias)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Levine, Arnold S.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>National Treasury Employees Union (NTEU) pres Robert Tobias saysthat the tense relationship between career federal employees andpolitical appointees breeds waste and inefficiency and leads toabuses in government personnel policy.andP;  Tobias notes that currentpay policies are stifling recruitment efforts and causing highturnover because salaries are not competitive and fail to takelocal costs of living into account.andP;  The Office of PersonnelManagement's locality-based pay plan, endorsed by NTEU, would letpersonnel officials adjust pay rates and job requirementsaccording to local market conditions.andP;  NTEU criticizes otherpersonnel initiatives such as those that call for contracting outquasi-commercial activities and delegating direct-hire authorityto agencies.andP;  Tobias also states that NTEU advocates the idea oflaws delegating personnel authority to agencies.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     National Treasury Employees UnionEmployee RelationsGovernment AgencyHiring.andO;Feature:   illustrationportrait.andO;Caption:   Robert Tobias. (portrait)Person:    Tobias, Robert (attitudes).andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>